cell("markdown","### Chalkboard Defense\nExplain how the binary search approach reduces the time complexity from $O(N)$ to $O(\\log N)$, and provide the exact condition used to determine whether to search the left or right half of the array.\n\n<details><summary>💡 Sketch</summary>\nInstead of checking every element sequentially, binary search checks the middle element of the cumulative array. If $r > \\text{cumulative}[\\text{mid}]$, the target must be in the right half. If $r \\leq \\text{cumulative}[\\text{mid}]$, it must be in the left half (including mid). This halves the search space at each step, taking $\\log_2 N$ steps.\n</details>\n\n---\n📚 **Next:** Algorithms 06 (Cartesian Product)")
